4 consutum] 29. 5n. The summoning of all available senators to such a meeting is not very often mentioned: it is done however, not only by the aristocrat Metellus, but also by the democratic Marius (104. 1). Pompey's counier-senate at Thessalonica would stand on a similar footing.
